The Trump Admin’s new policy is abominable.

Children born to service members and other government employees must automatically be citizens.

Our service members and public servants are working for the safety and security of our country and they deserve far better than this. https://twitter.com/politico/status/1166832097459351552 …

In March, @HouseDemocrats passed the Paycheck Fairness Act to strengthen protections against gender-based wage discrimination.

We will continue our work on closing the wage gap, guaranteeing paid family leave, expanding affordable childcare, & respecting women’s right to choose.

With the adoption of the 19th Amendment 99 years ago, we moved toward becoming a more fair society.

On #WomensEqualityDay, we celebrate the progress we made on that day & in the years since.

But, we must also continue to work to empower all women to reach their full potential.

This month, we mark the 400th anniversary of enslaved Africans arriving on this continent.
 
We must take this moment to reflect on our past and have honest, candid conversations that seek to heal our nation's wounds. https://www.baltimoresun.com/maryland/bs-ap-slavery-maryland-20190819-20190823-2igyor4hbvcspcmdzolwcu3rjq-story.html …

In 2017, Black women earned, on average, $0.61 for every $1.00 made by white, non-Hispanic male workers.

Today, we must acknowledge that the pay gap is compounded by race. 

Men and women, regardless of race, deserve #EqualPayForEqualWork.

#BlackWomenEqualPay

Congratulations to @DrLeanaWen for starting her next journey at @GWPublicHealth. 

I’m sure that her experience and dedication to delivering the best health outcomes to those in need will make her an invaluable resource for the next generation of public health leaders. https://twitter.com/baltimoresun/status/1163860374015418368 …

Every day, I wake up with one goal: to make sure our children & generations yet unborn will reach their God-given potential—& that the future we are creating is a brighter one for every child.  

I appreciate all we learned today about the work being done to achieve that goal.
I was pleased to be joined by federal, state, & city leaders; experts; service providers; & trauma survivors who are working to make our city stronger & safer for children.

Today, I hosted a forum on preventing, treating, & healing childhood trauma in Baltimore City.

Trauma can be prevented—& the effects of traumatic experiences can be identified & children who have experienced it can become thriving adults. pic.twitter.com/Dr5od0Vexy

Today, I am hosting a forum with trauma survivors, experts, service providers, and Baltimore City representatives and officials about childhood trauma and how we can prevent, treat, and heal it. 

Tune in live at 10:00 AM: https://m.youtube.com/channel/UCXSlyao4qkUFiPqghptHtZA …

The science is clear.

Traumatic experiences can injure the developing brains of children, create life-long impairments to their ability to manage stress and regulate emotions, and significantly increase the likelihood of negative health outcomes and even death.

With Planned Parenthood being forced out of the Title X program, the effect of the Trump Admin’s ideologically-motivated gag rule is clear. It will be harder for millions of Americans to access the healthcare they need. The Admin must reverse course immediately. https://twitter.com/AP/status/1163527253629841408 …

In February, I helped the House pass #HR8, the Bipartisan Background Checks Act, to require background checks for firearm transfers between private parties.
 
The Senate must consider this legislation immediately.

We must act for our children & the generations yet unborn.

Today, I joined advocates in Baltimore at a rally honoring all the lives tragically lost to gun violence.
 
I hear the urgent pleas from my constituents who are begging for more than thoughts and prayers.

Enough is enough.

We must #DoSomething to end gun violence. pic.twitter.com/Nsqg7Ass0x

I thank him for bringing light and beauty to this crisis. pic.twitter.com/b0KWT3mQHm

Voting is our democratic right, & allows us to control our destiny.

I thank @senatorCardin, @ChrisVanHollen, @LeaderHoyer, @Call_Me_Dutch, @RepSarbanes, @RepAnthonyBrown, @RepRaskin, & @RepDavidTrone for joining me on this important letter.

Our release:  https://cummings.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/maryland-congressional-delegation-presses-governor-hogan-ensure-all …

Today, Team Maryland & I sent a letter to Governor Hogan urging him to make meaningful improvements to voter registration, voter access, & election security to ensure that Marylanders can exercise their constitutional right to vote in the 2020 elections.

Voting is our democratic right, & allows us to control our destiny.

I thank @SenatorCardin, @ChrisValHollen, @LeaderHoyer, @Call_Me_Dutch, @RepSarbanes, @RepAnthonyBrown, @RepRaskin, & @RepDavidTrone for joining me on this important letter.

My heart is heavy to learn of the passing of Toni Morrison.

Her award-winning words brought life to the African-American experience & provided the sometimes hard truths about what it means to be a part of that legacy.

My thoughts and prayers are with her family & loved ones.

Voting is our democratic right, and allows us to control our destiny.

Today, on the 54th anniversary of the landmark #VotingRightsAct, make sure you are registered to vote so you can make your voice heard.

Find out how to register:  https://vote.gov/

I am horrified to learn of a second mass shooting in less than 24 hours. My soul aches for the Dayton community. 

This must stop. 

I pray for the victims & their loved ones, & I thank all the first responders. May God watch over everyone affected by this tragedy. #NeverAgain

Outdoor spaces like this bring life to life. 

Our children are the living messengers we send to a future we will never see, and it is so vital they have outdoor places like this to play right here in their community.

Further, I want to thank all the people of Baltimore who make projects like this happen throughout our community. 

It is an honor to work with you.

I want to thank the Druid Heights Community Development Corporation, the National Wildlife Foundation, the Chesapeake Bay Trust, the University of Maryland, and all the community organizations and volunteers who made this space possible.

Today, I was delighted to speak at the grand opening of the Druid Heights Community Development Corporation’s Nature Play Space on McCulloh Street. 

It went from a vacant lot used for dumping, to an outdoor area for kids to play and the community to gather. pic.twitter.com/uieWIaWbGb

I am heartbroken to learn about the mass shooting in El Paso. My prayers are with the victims and their families and I thank the first responders for their swift actions. 

For the sake of our children and generations yet unborn, this must stop. #NeverAgain
I thank Michael Bloomberg, the Bloomberg Foundation, Goldman Sachs, and the many sponsors of Baltimore‘s YouthWorks Program for believing in and helping Baltimore‘s youth.

Today, I spoke at the YouthWorks Fellowship graduation ceremony. The hard work and dedication of these young men and women always amazes me. Over the summer, the fellows earned pay while getting firsthand experience working in the public, private, and non-profit sectors. pic.twitter.com/owYfdTcnMO
